cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with image segmentation and synthesis using mixture models and deep networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of regularization and optimization techniques, which are common in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves the use of probabilistic generative models, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep networks also suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with multilayer segmentation and synthesis, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia).
